  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "An issue has been discovered in GitLab CE/EE affecting all versions starting from 11.9. GitLab was not properly validating image files that were passed to a file parser which resulted in a remote command execution.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2021-22205 describes an unauthenticated remote code execution vulnerability in GitLab CE/EE via improper validation of image files passed to a parser. GitLab is widely used in AI/ML pipelines for build/test/deploy and artifact management, so a vulnerability in this component constitutes a software supply-chain risk for general-purpose AI systems. The issue is clearly a security vulnerability with high impact, and the report provides concrete details and CVSS metrics."
